  "id": "http-server-ts-openapi-release-recovery",
  "courseId": "http-servers-typescript",
  "title": "OpenAPI 3.2, Compatibility, Deployment, Draining, and Recovery",
  "description": "Documentation differs from runtime, examples contain secrets, additive changes break strict clients, storage contracts before old revisions drain, and rollback cannot restore invariants. Learners cumulatively produce versioned API contract and production release defense through theory, guided work, debugging, transfer, retrieval, and assessment.",
  "order": 24,
  "objectives": [
    "Describe operations, parameters, request bodies, responses, schemas, security, callbacks, webhooks, examples, links, servers, and reusable components in OpenAPI 3.2.",
    "Choose a source of truth and gate generated clients, runtime validation, examples, operation IDs, security behavior, unknown fields, and spec-to-service drift.",
    "Classify additive and breaking changes across fields, nullability, validation, ordering, status, errors, authentication, caching, timing, and business behavior."
  ],
